post_text:
FCCLA Champions

Last week several FCCLA members participation in the Regional STAR Event Competition. The students had a very good showing for Kellyville and had other chapters make comments on how well our school did.

Those that competed were: Teyte Holcomb & Summer Archer - Promote and Publicize JR; Sierra Smith, Emily Carroll & Gracie Williams - Illustrated Talk SR (they planned a cancer project for those being treated at the chemo center); Lydia Pell - Life Event Planning JR; Aubree Dickard - Illustrated Talk JR (Epidermylosis Bulosa Project); Jessie-Dayle Hammons - Career Investigation JR; and Jaydee Pulliam & Grace Littlefield - Focus on Children (Foster Care Project).

First place winners go to Summer & Teyte and Sierra, Emily & Gracie. Congratulations! They will be competing at State on March 30. Other awards went to Lydia - 2nd Place and Jessie - 3rd Place. Everyone did a fantastic job! Way to go Kellyville!

Mrs. Speck want to make sure her students have the materials they need to succeed, so she created a request for her classroom at DonorsChoose.org: Chromebooks for Revving Up Our Spinning Minds.

Give to her classroom by January 21 and your donation will be doubled thanks to DonorsChoose.org. Just enter the code LIFTOFF on the payment page and you'll be matched dollar for dollar (up to $50).

Also Google.com will match dollar for dollar until the end of the project.

Mrs. Speck can be reached at speckd@kellyvilleschools.org

If you chip in to help my students, you'll get awesome photos and our heartfelt thanks.

post_text: Kellyville FFA will be partnering with the Kellyville Fire Department for their annual Christmas Toy Drive. We are sponsoring a contest for Middle School students with the winning grade receiving class points for 1st and 2nd place as well as 5 points for Each toy donated. The contest will begin Monday November 28 and End Thursday December 15th. Toys should be NEW in their original packages for ages 13 and under. All of the toys will go to children in the Kellyville Community and will be delivered by the Kellyville Fire Department.
